name: Shane Harris
tweet: Fair amount of detail here, building on Burns' testimony Wednesday, and Haines today on where the major homeland terrorist threats are located--i.e., not in Afghanistan. The bet here is AQ and ISIS don't have a foothold in Afghanistan now, and they're not likely to regain it.

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Rep. Kelly, who was shot at during the congressional softball practice, says an FBI agent never talked to him and "it was a political assassination," "it was an act of terror" and not "suicide by cop."

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Rep. Mullins questions Wray why he can't state the number of federal officers injured in protests in Portland. Asks if the FBI takes the Jan. 6 attack more seriously than attacks on federal buildings and personnel in Portland (by "left wing" and "Antifa".) Continuing a theme...

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Burns said he has met w/ different groups in his first weeks on the job of people affected by the "Havana Syndrome" of unexplained headaches, pain, and other issues affecting some intelligence officers, which some have attributed to a Russian attack.

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Rep. Swalwell asks Wray if FBI is looking at Q Anon as a "vector" for extremism. Wray says not investigating it per se that way, but describes it as a kind of inspiration for some violent acts. In his Senate testimony, as today, Wray emphasized the FBI doesn't investigate speech.

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Crawford returns to the Carter Page FISA and the FBI's actions, which Wray notes are being investigated by John Durham. As part of that, "There have been a number of instances...we have had to slow down or pause our internal disciplinary process" so as not to jeopardize the inv.

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Quigley asks Wray to elaborate on his earlier Antifa comments. Stresses he is not minimizing Antifa danger even though it's not "organized" in the same way as other extremists groups often are.

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Burns tells Rep. Quigley "we all have to take very seriously" the buildup of Russian troops along the border w/ Ukraine. Could be "signaling" to the US or meant to intimidate Ukraine. A "watching this space" message from Burns.

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Stewart is arguing that the NCTC is effectively a backdoor to let the intelligence community spy on and "target" US persons. More here on NCTC, which grew out of actions taken in 2003 by President Bush following the 9/11 attacks.  https://t.co/2jtpILoCzl

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Haines explains that the National Counterterrorism Center, which did the report, has statutory authority to receive intelligence on these issues. "It allows the NCTC to bring together domestic and international intelligence."

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Rep. Stewart asks Haines, "Should the CIA be spying on American citizens?" She says no, as do Burns and Nakasone. Then turns to a report on domestic violent extremism, stressing the word "domestic." "Did you use IC resources to write a report about domestic terrorism."

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Rep. Speier also w/ very tough questions for Wray, these on allegations of sexual misconduct and harassment by senior bureau officials. Tells him his answers are "not good enough" and will follow up.

name: Shane Harris
tweet: ...that the FBI is somehow out to get Republicans. Spying on them. Not taking attacks on them seriously enough. Wray says his assessment "differs greatly" from Wenstrup's characterization that the public has lost faith in the bureau.

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Wenstrup says the FBI has not classified the shooting as an act of "domestic terrorism," and rather calls it "suicide by cop." Notes that Andrew McCabe was the acting FBI director at the time. Wenstrup is continuing a theme, established by Nunes at the opening...

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Rep. Wenstrup recalls the 2017 shooting at a congressional softball practice, calling it "an insurrection" by an attacker who may have believed he could "change the balance of power" in the Congress by assassinating Republicans.

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Haines, re: a Q from Rep. Carson, IDs the areas "most concerning" as potential launchpad for a terrorist attack against the U.S. homeland. For Al Qaeda, it's Somalia, Syria, and Yemen. For ISIS, Iraq and Syrian, "where ISIS remains a capable insurgent group."

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Turner presses on whether Antifa has "financial support" and "coordinated" targeting. On financial, FBI still investigating and on targeting, has seen local groups coordinate on attacks, Wray says. Turner driving at whether there is some over-arching commander (my term) of Antifa

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Rep. Turner asks Wray if Antifa is a movement or "organization." Wray says there are individual or regional "nodes" and people who self-identify w/ Antifa, which is "a real thing." Turner presses, is there a coordinator, in essence. Wray says, "We're talking past each other."

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Haines lays out the argument for pushing back not only to deter further aggression, but to lend legitimacy to U.S. response to cyber attacks.

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Rep. Himes notes cyber attackers are "totally undeterred" in hitting the U.S. This came up several times in the Senate hearing yesterday, that there are no clear lines for foreign adversaries in the cyber domain.

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Nunes asks NSA Director Nakasone if he was ever "pressured" by a senior political leader to "recall" a report. ??? For the record, the director replied, "Absolutely not." Not entirely clear what the ranking member was getting at. Moving on.

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Nunes says the FBI spied on Republicans, "the opposition party," calling it "a hallmark of banana republics." Nunes then says he will submit questions for the record. IOW, he does not let Wray respond now to his accusations that the FBI was illegally spying on Republicans.

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Ranking Member Nunes using his opening questions in the global threats hearing to ask the FBI Director about Chris Steele and the FISA warrant on Carter Page. Says FBI has committed "outright lies" in Republicans' investigation of the same.

name: Shane Harris
tweet: FBI Director Wray says that a lot of domestic extremists "don't fit into nice, neat, ideological buckets." There's a "salad bar" of motivations. Says 5 Eyes partners see same. A "mishmash" of ideologies mixed w/ personal grievance. Often more about the violence than ideology.

name: Shane Harris
tweet: That's a wrap. Committee breaks for lunch, will reconvene with officials in a closed, classified session. The same witnesses will be in the House tomorrow for their version of the annual hearing, which maybe will be a little spicier. We'll see.

name: Shane Harris
tweet: It also must be said these officials are getting a very light touch from the committee members, who agree w/ them on most issues. Also just a striking lack of discussion on domestic violent extremism. Not zero, but not a lot!

name: Shane Harris
tweet: @emptywheel There is no doubt that she stands in stark contrast to her predecessors.

name: Shane Harris
tweet: This hearing feels more like a think tank discussion and an actual effort to speed through the list of massively complex issues that, in many respects, were neglected during this public process in the last 4 years.

name: Shane Harris
tweet: The posture and tone of this hearing is completely different than it was in previous years--when it actually happened. Trump was the elephant in the room then. Intel officials were scared to say something that might set him off--about Iran, North Korea, or (third rail) Russia.

name: Shane Harris
tweet: FBI Director Wray says the bureau focuses primarily on violence and threats of violence. Clearly concerned that the FBI not get into the business of policing speech (my characterization).

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Sen. Heinrich now asking about Jan. 6 and specifically the role Q Anon played in radicalizing people prior to that event. He's hamstrung to a degree, because he's referring to a document from the FBI that they won't fully declassify.

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Other things we're not hearing a lot about: The attack on the building in which this hearing is being held.

name: Shane Harris
tweet: @dnvolz Cyber pork is calorie free.

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Not yet hearing many questions on Afghanistan pullout. Burr asked Haines if she was "at the table" when the decision was made. She said she was present for various discussions leading up to it. Burr then says (frustratingly) he'll reserve questions for classified session.

name: Shane Harris
tweet: And notably, NSA Director Nakasone says his agency is continuing to gather information that might help answer these questions, and is working with US intel agencies, as well as other countries and "academia."

name: Shane Harris
tweet: CIA Director Burns agrees and says that China "has not been fully forthcoming or fully transparent...in providing the kind of original complete data that would help answer those questions."

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Haines, speaking for the IC, says they "do not know exactly where, when, or how" the coronavirus emerged. Theories have coalesced around 2 scenarios--natural transmission (animals to humans) or a lab accident. The IC is still investigating.

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Rubio uses his first questions to ask about the so-called "lab leak" theory that the virus that causes Covid-19 may have originated in the Wuhan Institute of Virology.

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Haines goes on to summarize the world of threats, from Iran, North Korea, cyber attacks, climate change, etc. ‚ÄúThat was a list of about as many awful things in ten minutes as I have heard in some time,‚Äù committee chairman Warner says.

name: Shane Harris
tweet: Russia will continue to deploy a range of tactics to undermine U.S. influence, but "Russia does not want a conflict with the United States," Haines says.
